And so if the package is on GitHub, as I mentioned, I'm not on CRAN yet.

00:14:16.780 --> 00:14:23.979
And so once you install the package using DevTools and you load it, you can follow our

00:14:23.979 --> 00:14:31.820
workflow, which starts by finding a source for package information using the package

00:14:31.820 --> 00:14:33.260
reference function.

00:14:33.260 --> 00:14:38.539
And it will look for packages installed, locally installed or on CRAN or Git.

00:14:39.979 --> 00:14:45.260
Once you have applied the package reference function, you can move on to assess.

00:14:45.260 --> 00:14:50.780
So what that will do is look at the different metrics and find information for the different

00:14:50.780 --> 00:14:56.539
metrics for the metrics as vignettes and news currents and so on.

00:14:56.539 --> 00:15:04.700
And lastly, you can apply the package score function, which will score the package based

00:15:04.700 --> 00:15:06.780
on the assessment criteria on those metrics.

00:15:08.700 --> 00:15:18.059
So then the results will be assembled in a data set that contains the overall risk and

00:15:18.059 --> 00:15:19.340
the other metrics.

